text:
56:33 "Where is this game- like where does the story- what's the lore"
Tfw a rabbit hole brings you down another rabbit hole

Also as a disclaimer, I only remember this from years ago. Spoilers ahead! You can investigate and go into detail of what happened with each character like how Abigail died and how the latest official video for Wendy confirms the investigation.
Let me tell you about Don't Starve
For anyone wondering, the lore at least starts with Maxwell (the main antagonist and the one who greets you at the start of the original game) as a stage performer, a magician. He gets his hands on the Codex Umbra and performs it in his next magic show but it goes horribly wrong. While trying to pull something out of the book, Maxwell resists being pulled in but in the end, it grabs both him and his assistant Charlie (who later becomes the "Darkness" or the game's version of the Grue). Maxwell is brought into the world of Don't Starve (which fans call The Constant but is generally referred to as Maxwell's world) and becomes the first ruler and creator of the world. Although he notes that some things have already existed before he's entered.
(There is an official video for this, please check it out) The original game starts with Wilson, a scientist experimenting to find something new. Maxwell calls Wilson through a radio and grants him forbidden knowledge, a portal that grabs him into The Constant. Maxwell greets Wilson (or whoever the player is playing as) and tells them to gather food before night falls. And from this point on, it's a survival-horror (if you find the low sanity effects as spooky which I do) game with Maxwell playing god every once in a while to send the hounds your way.
I was really hoping they'd show us their reaction to the game before they tested it cuz the night scared me shitless the first time I played it
